column3: DARTH SlDIOUS: His death was a necessary loss which will ensure our victory. Soon I will have a new apprentice . . . one far younger and more powerful than Lord Tyranus.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: His death was a necessary loss which will ensure our victory. Soon I will have a new apprentice . . . one far younger and more powerful than Lord Tyranus.

column3: ANAKIN: . . . every second I was thinking of you. Protecting the endless nameless Outer Rim settlements became a torture . . . the battles were easy the longing became unbearable . . . I've never been so happy as I am at this moment.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: . . . every second I was thinking of you. Protecting the endless nameless Outer Rim settlements became a torture . . . the battles were easy the longing became unbearable . . . I've never been so happy as I am at this moment.

column3: PADME: Annie I want to have our baby back home on Naboo. We could go to the lake country where no one would know . . . where we would be safe. I could go early-and fix up the baby's room. I know the perfect spot right by the gardens.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Annie I want to have our baby back home on Naboo. We could go to the lake country where no one would know . . . where we would be safe. I could go early-and fix up the baby's room. I know the perfect spot right by the gardens.

column3: ANAKIN: You are so beautiful!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You are so beautiful!

column3: PADME: It's only because I'm so in love . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It's only because I'm so in love . . .

column3: ANAKIN: No it's because I'm so in love with you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: No it's because I'm so in love with you.

column3: PADME: So love has blinded you?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: So love has blinded you?

column3: ANAKIN: Well that's not exactly what I meant . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Well that's not exactly what I meant . . .

column3: PADME: But it's probably true!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: But it's probably true!

column3: ANAKIN: I haven't laughed in so long . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I haven't laughed in so long . . .

column3: PADME: Neither have I.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Neither have I.

column3: PADME: Anakin help me! Help Anakin! Anakin I love you. I love you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin help me! Help Anakin! Anakin I love you. I love you.

column3: PADME: Anakin??NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin??

column3: PADME: What's bothering you?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What's bothering you?

column3: ANAKIN: Nothing . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Nothing . . .

column3: ANAKIN: (continuing) I remember when I gave this to you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I remember when I gave this to you.

column3: PADME: Anakin how long is it going to take for us to be honest with each other?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin how long is it going to take for us to be honest with each other?

column3: ANAKIN: It was a dream.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It was a dream.

column3: PADME: Bad?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Bad?

column3: ANAKIN: Like the ones I used to have about my mother just before she died.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Like the ones I used to have about my mother just before she died.

column3: PADME: And?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And?

column3: ANAKIN: It was about you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It was about you.

column3: PADME: Tell me.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Tell me.

column3: ANAKIN: It was only a dream.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It was only a dream.

column3: ANAKIN: (continuing) You die in childbirth . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You die in childbirth . . .

column3: PADME: And the baby?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And the baby?

column3: ANAKIN: I don't know.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I don't know.

column3: PADME: It was only a dream.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It was only a dream.

column3: ANAKIN: . . . I won't let this one become real Padme.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: . . . I won't let this one become real Padme.

column3: PADME: Anakin this baby will change our lives. I doubt the Queen will continue to allow me to serve in the Senate and if the Council discovers you are the father you will be expelled from the Jedi Order.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin this baby will change our lives. I doubt the Queen will continue to allow me to serve in the Senate and if the Council discovers you are the father you will be expelled from the Jedi Order.

column3: ANAKIN: I know .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I know .

column3: PADME: Anakin do you think Obi-Wan might be able to help us?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin do you think Obi-Wan might be able to help us?

column3: ANAKIN: (suspicious) Have you told him anything?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Have you told him anything?

column3: PADME: No but he's your mentor your best friend . . . he must suspect something.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: No but he's your mentor your best friend . . . he must suspect something.

column3: ANAKIN: He's been a father to me but he's still on the Council. Don't tell him anything!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He's been a father to me but he's still on the Council. Don't tell him anything!

column3: PADME: I won't Anakin.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I won't Anakin.

column3: ANAKIN: I don't need his help . . . Our baby is a blessing not a problem.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I don't need his help . . . Our baby is a blessing not a problem.

column3: YODA: Premonitions . . . premonitions . . . Hmmmm . . . these visions you have . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Premonitions . . . premonitions . . . Hmmmm . . . these visions you have . . .

column3: ANAKIN: They are of pain suffering death . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They are of pain suffering death . . .

column3: YODA: Yourself you speak of or someone you know?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yourself you speak of or someone you know?

column3: ANAKIN: Someone . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Someone . . .

column3: YODA: . . . close to you?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: . . . close to you?

column3: ANAKIN: Yes.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes.

column3: YODA: Careful you must be when sensing the future Anakin. The fear of loss is a path to the dark side.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Careful you must be when sensing the future Anakin. The fear of loss is a path to the dark side.

column3: ANAKIN: I won't let these visions come true Master Yoda.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I won't let these visions come true Master Yoda.

column3: YODA: Death is a natural part of life. Rejoice for those around you who transform into the Force. Mourn them do not. Miss them do not. Attachment leads to jealousy. The shadow of greed that is.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Death is a natural part of life. Rejoice for those around you who transform into the Force. Mourn them do not. Miss them do not. Attachment leads to jealousy. The shadow of greed that is.

column3: ANAKIN: What must I do Master Yoda?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What must I do Master Yoda?

column3: YODA: Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.

column3: OBI-WAN: You missed the report on the Outer Rim sieges.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You missed the report on the Outer Rim sieges.

column3: ANAKIN: I'm sorry I was held up. I have no excuse.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I'm sorry I was held up. I have no excuse.

column3: OBI-WAN: In short they are going very well. Saleucami has fallen and Master Vos has moved his troops to Boz Pity.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: In short they are going very well. Saleucami has fallen and Master Vos has moved his troops to Boz Pity.

column3: ANAKIN: What's wrong then?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What's wrong then?

column3: OBI-WAN: The Senate is expected to vote more executive powers to the Chancellor today.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Senate is expected to vote more executive powers to the Chancellor today.

column3: ANAKIN: Well that can only mean less deliberating and more action. Is that bad? It will make it easier for us to end this war.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Well that can only mean less deliberating and more action. Is that bad? It will make it easier for us to end this war.

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin be careful of your friend Palpatine.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin be careful of your friend Palpatine.

column3: ANAKIN: Be careful of what?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Be careful of what?

column3: OBI-WAN: He has requested your presence.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He has requested your presence.

column3: ANAKIN: What for?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What for?

column3: OBI-WAN: He would not say.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He would not say.

column3: ANAKIN: He didn't inform the Jedi Council? That's unusual isn't it?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He didn't inform the Jedi Council? That's unusual isn't it?

column3: OBI-WAN: All of this is unusual and it's making me feel uneasy. You're probably aware that relations between the Council and the Chancellor are stressed.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: All of this is unusual and it's making me feel uneasy. You're probably aware that relations between the Council and the Chancellor are stressed.

column3: ANAKIN: I know the Council has grown wary of the Chancellor's power mine also for that matter. Aren't we all working together to save the Republic? Why all this distrust?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I know the Council has grown wary of the Chancellor's power mine also for that matter. Aren't we all working together to save the Republic? Why all this distrust?

column3: OBI-WAN: The Force grows dark Anakin and we are all affected by it. Be wary of your feelings.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Force grows dark Anakin and we are all affected by it. Be wary of your feelings.

column3: PALPATINE: Anakin this afternoon the Senate is going to call on me to take direct control of the Jedi Council.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin this afternoon the Senate is going to call on me to take direct control of the Jedi Council.

column3: ANAKIN: The Jedi will no longer report to the Senate?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Jedi will no longer report to the Senate?

column3: PALPATINE: They will report to me . . . personally. The Senate is too unfocused to conduct a war. This will bring a quick end to things.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They will report to me . . . personally. The Senate is too unfocused to conduct a war. This will bring a quick end to things.

column3: ANAKIN: I agree but the Jedi Council may not see it that way.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I agree but the Jedi Council may not see it that way.

column3: PALPATINE: There are times when we must all endure adjustments to the constitution in the name of security.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: There are times when we must all endure adjustments to the constitution in the name of security.

column3: ANAKIN: With all due respect sir the Council is in no mood for more constitutional amendments.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: With all due respect sir the Council is in no mood for more constitutional amendments.

column3: PALPATINE: Thank you my friend but in this case I have no choice . . . this war must be won.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Thank you my friend but in this case I have no choice . . . this war must be won.

column3: ANAKIN: Everyone will agree on that.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Everyone will agree on that.

column3: PALPATINE: Anakin I've known you since you were a small boy. I have advised you over the years when I could ... I am very proud of your accomplishments. You have won many battles the Jedi Council thought were lost . . . and you saved my life. I hope you trust me Anakin.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin I've known you since you were a small boy. I have advised you over the years when I could ... I am very proud of your accomplishments. You have won many battles the Jedi Council thought were lost . . . and you saved my life. I hope you trust me Anakin.

column3: ANAKIN: Of course.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Of course.

column3: PALPATINE: I need your help son.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I need your help son.

column3: ANAKIN: What do you mean?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What do you mean?

column3: PALPATINE: I fear the Jedi. The Council keeps pushing for more control. They're shrouded in secrecy and obsessed with maintaining their autonomy . . . ideals. I find simply incomprehensible in a democracy.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I fear the Jedi. The Council keeps pushing for more control. They're shrouded in secrecy and obsessed with maintaining their autonomy . . . ideals. I find simply incomprehensible in a democracy.

column3: ANAKIN: I can assure you that the Jedi are dedicated to the values of the Republic sir.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I can assure you that the Jedi are dedicated to the values of the Republic sir.

column3: PALPATINE: Nevertheless their actions will speak more loudly than their words. I'm depending on you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Nevertheless their actions will speak more loudly than their words. I'm depending on you.

column3: ANAKIN: For what? I don't understand.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: For what? I don't understand.

column3: PALPATINE: To be the eyes ears and voice of the Republic . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: To be the eyes ears and voice of the Republic . . .

column3: PALPATINE: (continuing) Anakin . . . I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin . . . I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.

column3: ANAKIN: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed sir but the Council elects its own members. They will never accept this.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed sir but the Council elects its own members. They will never accept this.

column3: PALPATINE: I think they will . . . they need you more than you know.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I think they will . . . they need you more than you know.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: Now that he has control of the Jedi Council the Chancellor has appointed Governors to oversee all star systems in the Republic.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Now that he has control of the Jedi Council the Chancellor has appointed Governors to oversee all star systems in the Republic.

column3: FANG ZAR: When did this happen?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: When did this happen?

column3: BAIL ORGANA: The decree was posted this morning.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The decree was posted this morning.

column3: PADME: Do you think he will dismantle the Senate?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Do you think he will dismantle the Senate?

column3: MON MOTHMA: Why bother? As a practical matter the Senate no longer exists.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Why bother? As a practical matter the Senate no longer exists.

column3: GIDDEAN DANU: The constitution is in shreds. Amendment after amendment . . . executive directives sometimes a dozen in one day.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The constitution is in shreds. Amendment after amendment . . . executive directives sometimes a dozen in one day.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: We can't let a thousand years of democracy disappear without a fight.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We can't let a thousand years of democracy disappear without a fight.

column3: TERR TANEEL: What are you suggesting?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What are you suggesting?

column3: BAIL ORGANA: I apologize. I didn't mean to sound like a Separatist.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I apologize. I didn't mean to sound like a Separatist.

column3: MON MOTHMA: We are not Separatists trying to leave the Republic. We are loyalists trying to preserve democracy in the Republic.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We are not Separatists trying to leave the Republic. We are loyalists trying to preserve democracy in the Republic.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: It has become increasingly clear to many of us that the Chancellor has become an enemy of democracy.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It has become increasingly clear to many of us that the Chancellor has become an enemy of democracy.

column3: PADME: I can't believe it has come to this! Chancellor Palpatine is one of my oldest advisors. He served as my Ambassador when I was Queen.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I can't believe it has come to this! Chancellor Palpatine is one of my oldest advisors. He served as my Ambassador when I was Queen.

column3: GlDDEAN DANU: Senator I fear you underestimate the amount of corruption that has taken hold in the Senate.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Senator I fear you underestimate the amount of corruption that has taken hold in the Senate.

column3: MON MOTHMA: The Chancellor has played the Senators well. They know where the power lies and they will do whatever it takes to share in it. Palpatine has become a dictator and we have helped him to do it.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Chancellor has played the Senators well. They know where the power lies and they will do whatever it takes to share in it. Palpatine has become a dictator and we have helped him to do it.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: We can't sit around debating any longer we have decided to do what we can to stop it. Senator Mon Mothma and I are putting together an organization . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We can't sit around debating any longer we have decided to do what we can to stop it. Senator Mon Mothma and I are putting together an organization . . .

column3: PADME: Say no more. Senator Organa. I understand. At this point it's better to leave some things unsaid.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Say no more. Senator Organa. I understand. At this point it's better to leave some things unsaid.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: Yes. I agree and we must not discuss this with anyone without everyone in this group agreeing.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes. I agree and we must not discuss this with anyone without everyone in this group agreeing.

column3: MON MOTHMA: That means those closest to you . . . even family ... no one can be told.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: That means those closest to you . . . even family ... no one can be told.

column3: PADME: Agreed.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Agreed.

column3: MACE: Anakin Skywalker we have approved your appointment to the Council as the Chancellor's personal representative.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin Skywalker we have approved your appointment to the Council as the Chancellor's personal representative.

column3: ANAKIN: I will do my best to uphold the principles of the Jedi Order.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I will do my best to uphold the principles of the Jedi Order.

column3: YODA: Allow this appointment lightly the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Allow this appointment lightly the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.

column3: ANAKIN: I understand.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I understand.

column3: MACE: You are on this Council but we do not grant you the rank of Master.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You are on this Council but we do not grant you the rank of Master.

column3: ANAKIN: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous it's unfair . . . I'm more powerful than any of you. How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous it's unfair . . . I'm more powerful than any of you. How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?

column3: MACE: Take a seat young Skywalker.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Take a seat young Skywalker.

column3: ANAKIN: Forgive me Master.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Forgive me Master.

column3: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic and have found no sign of General Grievous.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic and have found no sign of General Grievous.

column3: YODA: Hiding in the Outer Rim Grievous is. The outlying systems you must sweep.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Hiding in the Outer Rim Grievous is. The outlying systems you must sweep.

column3: OBI-WAN: It may take some time . . . we do not have many ships to spare.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It may take some time . . . we do not have many ships to spare.

column3: MACE: We cannot take ships from the front line.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We cannot take ships from the front line.

column3: OBI-WAN: And yet it would be fatal for us to allow the droid armies to regroup.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And yet it would be fatal for us to allow the droid armies to regroup.

column3: YODA: Master Kenobi our spies contact you must and then wait.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Master Kenobi our spies contact you must and then wait.

column3: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?

column3: MACE: It is critical we send an attack group there immediately!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It is critical we send an attack group there immediately!

column3: OBI-WAN: He's right that is a system we cannot afford to lose. It's the main navigation route for the southwestern quadrant.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He's right that is a system we cannot afford to lose. It's the main navigation route for the southwestern quadrant.

column3: ANAKIN: I know that system well. It would take us little time to drive the droids off that planet.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I know that system well. It would take us little time to drive the droids off that planet.

column3: MACE: Skywalker your assignment is here with the Chancellor and Kenobi must find General Grievous.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Skywalker your assignment is here with the Chancellor and Kenobi must find General Grievous.

column3: YODA: Go I will. Good relations with the Wookiees I have.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Go I will. Good relations with the Wookiees I have.

column3: MACE: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.

column3: ANAKIN: What kind of nonsense is this put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What kind of nonsense is this put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!

column3: OBI-WAN: Calm down Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age . . . It's never happened before. Listen to me Anakin. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Calm down Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age . . . It's never happened before. Listen to me Anakin. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.

column3: ANAKIN: I swear to you I didn't ask to be put on the Council . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I swear to you I didn't ask to be put on the Council . . .

column3: OBI-WAN: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.

column3: ANAKIN: That has nothing to do with this.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: That has nothing to do with this.

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin regardless of how it happened you find yourself in a delicate situation.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin regardless of how it happened you find yourself in a delicate situation.

column3: ANAKIN: You mean divided loyalties.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You mean divided loyalties.

column3: OBI-WAN: I warned you there was tension between the Council and the Chancellor. I was very clear. Why didn't you listen? You walked right into it.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I warned you there was tension between the Council and the Chancellor. I was very clear. Why didn't you listen? You walked right into it.

column3: ANAKIN: The Council is upset I'm the youngest to ever serve.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Council is upset I'm the youngest to ever serve.

column3: OBI-WAN: No it is not. Anakin I worry when you speak of jealousy and pride. Those are not Jedi thoughts. They're dangerous dark thoughts.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: No it is not. Anakin I worry when you speak of jealousy and pride. Those are not Jedi thoughts. They're dangerous dark thoughts.

column3: ANAKIN: Master you of all people should have confidence in my abilities. I know where my loyalties lie.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Master you of all people should have confidence in my abilities. I know where my loyalties lie.

column3: OBI-WAN: I hope so . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I hope so . . .

column3: ANAKIN: I sense there's more to this talk than you're saying.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I sense there's more to this talk than you're saying.

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin the only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin the only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.

column3: ANAKIN: And?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And?

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin look I am on your side. I didn't want to see you put in this situation.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin look I am on your side. I didn't want to see you put in this situation.

column3: ANAKIN: What situation?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What situation?

column3: OBI-WAN: (takes a deep breath) The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.

column3: ANAKIN: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!

column3: OBI-WAN: We are at war Anakin. The Jedi Council is sworn to uphold the principles of the Republic even if the Chancellor does not.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We are at war Anakin. The Jedi Council is sworn to uphold the principles of the Republic even if the Chancellor does not.

column3: ANAKIN: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?

column3: OBI-WAN: This assignment is not to be on record. The Council asked me to approach you on this personally.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: This assignment is not to be on record. The Council asked me to approach you on this personally.

column3: ANAKIN: The Chancellor is not a bad man Obi-Wan. He befriended me. He's watched out for me ever since I arrived here.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone

column3: MACE:I wish I did.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I wish I did.

column6: He will not let me down. He never has.

column6: Patience. In time they will recognize your skills.

column6: Anakin . . .

column6: What if the democracy we thought we were serving no longer exists and the Republic has become the very evil we have been fighting to destroy?

column6: I don't believe that. And you're sounding like a Separatist!

column6: Anakin this war represents a failure to listen . . . Now you're closer to the Chancellor than anyone. Please please ask him to stop the fighting and let diplomacy resume.

column6: Don't ask me to do that Padme. Make a motion in the Senate where that kind of a request belongs. I'm not your errand boy. I'm not anyone's errand boy!

column6: Don't do this . . . don't shut me out. Let me help you.

column6: You can't help me . . . I'm trying to help you.

column6: I sense . . . there are things you are not telling me.

column6: I sense there are things you are not telling me.

column6: Hold me . . . like you did by the lake on Naboo so long ago . . . when there was nothing but our love ... No politics no plotting ... no war.

column6: You wanted to see me Chancellor.

column6: Yes Anakin! Come closer. I have good news. Our Clone Intelligence Units have discovered the location of General Grievous. He is hiding in the Utapau system.

column6: At last we'll be able to capture that monster and end this war.

column6: I would worry about the collective wisdom of the Council if they didn't select you for this assignment. You are the best choice by far  but they can't always be trusted to do the right thing.

column6: Sit down  Leave us.

column6: Anakin you know I'm not able to rely on the Jedi Council. If they haven't included you in their plot they soon will.

column6: I'm not sure I understand.

column6: You must sense what I have come to suspect . . . the Jedi Council want control of the Republic . . . they're planning to betray me.

column6: I know they don't trust you . . .

column6: Or the Senate . . . or the Republic . . . or democracy for that matter.

column6: I have to admit my trust in them has been shaken.

column6: Why? They asked you to do something that made you feel dishonest didn't they?

column6: I don't know ... I don't know what to say.

He had such a knowledge of the dark side that he could even keep the ones he cared about from dying.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone

column3: OBI-WAN: You are strong and wise Anakin and I am very proud of you. I have trained you since you were a small boy. I have taught you everything I know. column3: PALPATINE: (continuing) Anakin . . . I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin . . . I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.

column3: ANAKIN: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed sir but the Council elects its own members. They will never accept this.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed sir but the Council elects its own members. They will never accept this.

column3: PALPATINE: I think they will . . . they need you more than you know.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I think they will . . . they need you more than you know.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: Now that he has control of the Jedi Council the Chancellor has appointed Governors to oversee all star systems in the Republic.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Now that he has control of the Jedi Council the Chancellor has appointed Governors to oversee all star systems in the Republic.

column3: FANG ZAR: When did this happen?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: When did this happen?

column3: BAIL ORGANA: The decree was posted this morning.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The decree was posted this morning.

column3: PADME: Do you think he will dismantle the Senate?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Do you think he will dismantle the Senate?

column3: MON MOTHMA: Why bother? As a practical matter the Senate no longer exists.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Why bother? As a practical matter the Senate no longer exists.

column3: GIDDEAN DANU: The constitution is in shreds. Amendment after amendment . . . executive directives sometimes a dozen in one day.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The constitution is in shreds. Amendment after amendment . . . executive directives sometimes a dozen in one day.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: We can't let a thousand years of democracy disappear without a fight.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We can't let a thousand years of democracy disappear without a fight.

column3: TERR TANEEL: What are you suggesting?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What are you suggesting?

column3: BAIL ORGANA: I apologize. I didn't mean to sound like a Separatist.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I apologize. I didn't mean to sound like a Separatist.

column3: MON MOTHMA: We are not Separatists trying to leave the Republic. We are loyalists trying to preserve democracy in the Republic.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We are not Separatists trying to leave the Republic. We are loyalists trying to preserve democracy in the Republic.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: It has become increasingly clear to many of us that the Chancellor has become an enemy of democracy.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It has become increasingly clear to many of us that the Chancellor has become an enemy of democracy.

column3: PADME: I can't believe it has come to this! Chancellor Palpatine is one of my oldest advisors. He served as my Ambassador when I was Queen.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I can't believe it has come to this! Chancellor Palpatine is one of my oldest advisors. He served as my Ambassador when I was Queen.

column3: GlDDEAN DANU: Senator I fear you underestimate the amount of corruption that has taken hold in the Senate.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Senator I fear you underestimate the amount of corruption that has taken hold in the Senate.

column3: MON MOTHMA: The Chancellor has played the Senators well. They know where the power lies and they will do whatever it takes to share in it. Palpatine has become a dictator and we have helped him to do it.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Chancellor has played the Senators well. They know where the power lies and they will do whatever it takes to share in it. Palpatine has become a dictator and we have helped him to do it.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: We can't sit around debating any longer we have decided to do what we can to stop it. Senator Mon Mothma and I are putting together an organization . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We can't sit around debating any longer we have decided to do what we can to stop it. Senator Mon Mothma and I are putting together an organization . . .

column3: PADME: Say no more. Senator Organa. I understand. At this point it's better to leave some things unsaid.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Say no more. Senator Organa. I understand. At this point it's better to leave some things unsaid.

column3: BAIL ORGANA: Yes. I agree and we must not discuss this with anyone without everyone in this group agreeing.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes. I agree and we must not discuss this with anyone without everyone in this group agreeing.

column3: MON MOTHMA: That means those closest to you . . . even family ... no one can be told.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: That means those closest to you . . . even family ... no one can be told.

column3: PADME: Agreed.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Agreed.

column3: MACE: Anakin Skywalker we have approved your appointment to the Council as the Chancellor's personal representative.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin Skywalker we have approved your appointment to the Council as the Chancellor's personal representative.

column3: ANAKIN: I will do my best to uphold the principles of the Jedi Order.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I will do my best to uphold the principles of the Jedi Order.

column3: YODA: Allow this appointment lightly the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Allow this appointment lightly the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.

column3: ANAKIN: I understand.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I understand.

column3: MACE: You are on this Council but we do not grant you the rank of Master.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You are on this Council but we do not grant you the rank of Master.

column3: ANAKIN: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous it's unfair . . . I'm more powerful than any of you. How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous it's unfair . . . I'm more powerful than any of you. How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?

column3: MACE: Take a seat young Skywalker.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Take a seat young Skywalker.

column3: ANAKIN: Forgive me Master.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Forgive me Master.

column3: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic and have found no sign of General Grievous.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic and have found no sign of General Grievous.

column3: YODA: Hiding in the Outer Rim Grievous is. The outlying systems you must sweep.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Hiding in the Outer Rim Grievous is. The outlying systems you must sweep.

column3: OBI-WAN: It may take some time . . . we do not have many ships to spare.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It may take some time . . . we do not have many ships to spare.

column3: MACE: We cannot take ships from the front line.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We cannot take ships from the front line.

column3: OBI-WAN: And yet it would be fatal for us to allow the droid armies to regroup.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And yet it would be fatal for us to allow the droid armies to regroup.

column3: YODA: Master Kenobi our spies contact you must and then wait.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Master Kenobi our spies contact you must and then wait.

column3: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?

column3: MACE: It is critical we send an attack group there immediately!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It is critical we send an attack group there immediately!

column3: OBI-WAN: He's right that is a system we cannot afford to lose. It's the main navigation route for the southwestern quadrant.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He's right that is a system we cannot afford to lose. It's the main navigation route for the southwestern quadrant.

column3: ANAKIN: I know that system well. It would take us little time to drive the droids off that planet.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I know that system well. It would take us little time to drive the droids off that planet.

column3: MACE: Skywalker your assignment is here with the Chancellor and Kenobi must find General Grievous.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Skywalker your assignment is here with the Chancellor and Kenobi must find General Grievous.

column3: YODA: Go I will. Good relations with the Wookiees I have.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Go I will. Good relations with the Wookiees I have.

column3: MACE: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.

column3: ANAKIN: What kind of nonsense is this put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What kind of nonsense is this put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!

column3: OBI-WAN: Calm down Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age . . . It's never happened before. Listen to me Anakin. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Calm down Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age . . . It's never happened before. Listen to me Anakin. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.

column3: ANAKIN: I swear to you I didn't ask to be put on the Council . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I swear to you I didn't ask to be put on the Council . . .

column3: OBI-WAN: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.

column3: ANAKIN: That has nothing to do with this.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: That has nothing to do with this.

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin regardless of how it happened you find yourself in a delicate situation.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin regardless of how it happened you find yourself in a delicate situation.

column3: ANAKIN: You mean divided loyalties.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You mean divided loyalties.

column3: OBI-WAN: I warned you there was tension between the Council and the Chancellor. I was very clear. Why didn't you listen? You walked right into it.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I warned you there was tension between the Council and the Chancellor. I was very clear. Why didn't you listen? You walked right into it.

column3: ANAKIN: The Council is upset I'm the youngest to ever serve.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Council is upset I'm the youngest to ever serve.

column3: OBI-WAN: No it is not. Anakin I worry when you speak of jealousy and pride. Those are not Jedi thoughts. They're dangerous dark thoughts.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: No it is not. Anakin I worry when you speak of jealousy and pride. Those are not Jedi thoughts. They're dangerous dark thoughts.

column3: ANAKIN: Master you of all people should have confidence in my abilities. I know where my loyalties lie.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Master you of all people should have confidence in my abilities. I know where my loyalties lie.

column3: OBI-WAN: I hope so . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I hope so . . .

column3: ANAKIN: I sense there's more to this talk than you're saying.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I sense there's more to this talk than you're saying.

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin the only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin the only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.

column3: ANAKIN: And?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And?

column3: OBI-WAN: Anakin look I am on your side. I didn't want to see you put in this situation.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin look I am on your side. I didn't want to see you put in this situation.

column3: ANAKIN: What situation?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What situation?

column3: OBI-WAN: (takes a deep breath) The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.

column3: ANAKIN: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!

column3: OBI-WAN: We are at war Anakin. The Jedi Council is sworn to uphold the principles of the Republic even if the Chancellor does not.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: We are at war Anakin. The Jedi Council is sworn to uphold the principles of the Republic even if the Chancellor does not.

column3: ANAKIN: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?

column3: OBI-WAN: This assignment is not to be on record. The Council asked me to approach you on this personally.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: This assignment is not to be on record. The Council asked me to approach you on this personally.

column3: ANAKIN: The Chancellor is not a bad man Obi-Wan. He befriended me. He's watched out for me ever since I arrived here.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Chancellor is not a bad man Obi-Wan. He befriended me. He's watched out for me ever since I arrived here.

column3: OBI-WAN: That is why you must help us Anakin. Our allegiance is to the Senate not to its leader who has managed to stay in office long after his term has expired.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: That is why you must help us Anakin. Our allegiance is to the Senate not to its leader who has managed to stay in office long after his term has expired.

column3: ANAKIN: Master the Senate demanded that he stay longer.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Master the Senate demanded that he stay longer.

column3: OBI-WAN: Yes but use your feelings Anakin. Something is out of place.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes but use your feelings Anakin. Something is out of place.

column3: ANAKIN: You're asking me to do something against the Jedi Code. Against the Republic. Against a mentor . . . and a friend. That's what's out of place here. Why are you asking this of me?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You're asking me to do something against the Jedi Code. Against the Republic. Against a mentor . . . and a friend. That's what's out of place here. Why are you asking this of me?

column3: OBI-WAN: The Council is asking you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Council is asking you.

column3: OBI-WAN : Anakin did not take to his assignment with much enthusiasm.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin did not take to his assignment with much enthusiasm.

column3: YODA: Too much under the sway of the Chancellor he is. Much anger there is in him. Too much pride in his powers.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Too much under the sway of the Chancellor he is. Much anger there is in him. Too much pride in his powers.

column3: MACE: It's very dangerous putting them together. I don't think the boy can handle it. I don't trust him.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: It's very dangerous putting them together. I don't think the boy can handle it. I don't trust him.

column3: OBI-WAN: He'll be all right. I trust him with my life.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He'll be all right. I trust him with my life.

column3: MACE:I wish I did.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I wish I did.

column3: OBI-WAN: With all due respect Master is he not the Chosen One? Is he not to destroy the Sith and bring balance to the Force?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: With all due respect Master is he not the Chosen One? Is he not to destroy the Sith and bring balance to the Force?

column3: MACE: So the prophecy says.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: So the prophecy says.

column3: YODA: A prophecy . . . that misread could have been.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: A prophecy . . . that misread could have been.

column3: OBI-WAN: He will not let me down. He never has.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He will not let me down. He never has.

column3: YODA: I hope right you are. And now destroy the Droid armies on Kashyyyk I will. May the Force be with you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I hope right you are. And now destroy the Droid armies on Kashyyyk I will. May the Force be with you.

column3: PADME: Thank you Captain.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Thank you Captain.

column3: CAPTAIN TYPHO: Rest well. My Lady.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Rest well. My Lady.

column3: PADME: I'll be up in a while.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I'll be up in a while.

column3: MOTEE: Yes my lady.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes my lady.

column3: C-3PO: Is there anything I might do for you my lady?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Is there anything I might do for you my lady?

column3: PADME: Yes make sure all the security droids are working. Thank you Threepio.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes make sure all the security droids are working. Thank you Threepio.

column3: ANAKIN: Beautiful isn't it?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Beautiful isn't it?

column3: PADME: You startled me.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You startled me.

column3: ANAKIN: How are you feeling?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: How are you feeling?

column3: PADME: He keeps kicking.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He keeps kicking.

column3: ANAKIN: He?! Why do you think it's a boy?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: He?! Why do you think it's a boy?

column3: PADME: (laughs) My motherly intuition.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: My motherly intuition.

column3: ANAKIN: Whoa! With a kick that strong it's got to be a girl.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Whoa! With a kick that strong it's got to be a girl.

column3: PADME: I heard about your appointment. Anakin. I'm so proud of you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I heard about your appointment. Anakin. I'm so proud of you.

column3: ANAKIN: I may be on the Council but . . . they refused to accept me as a Jedi Master.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I may be on the Council but . . . they refused to accept me as a Jedi Master.

column3: PADME: Patience. In time they will recognize your skills.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Patience. In time they will recognize your skills.

column3: ANAKIN: They still treat me as if I were a Padawan learner. . . they fear my power that's the problem.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They still treat me as if I were a Padawan learner. . . they fear my power that's the problem.

column3: PADME: Anakin . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin . . .

column3: ANAKIN: Sometimes I wonder what's happening to the Jedi Order . . . I think this war is destroying the principles of the Republic.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Sometimes I wonder what's happening to the Jedi Order . . . I think this war is destroying the principles of the Republic.

column3: PADME: Have you ever considered that we may be on the wrong side?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Have you ever considered that we may be on the wrong side?

column3: ANAKIN: (suspicious) What do you mean?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What do you mean?

column3: PADME: What if the democracy we thought we were serving no longer exists and the Republic has become the very evil we have been fighting to destroy?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What if the democracy we thought we were serving no longer exists and the Republic has become the very evil we have been fighting to destroy?

column3: ANAKIN: I don't believe that. And you're sounding like a Separatist!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I don't believe that. And you're sounding like a Separatist!

column3: PADME: Anakin this war represents a failure to listen . . . Now you're closer to the Chancellor than anyone. Please please ask him to stop the fighting and let diplomacy resume.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin this war represents a failure to listen . . . Now you're closer to the Chancellor than anyone. Please please ask him to stop the fighting and let diplomacy resume.

column3: ANAKIN: (growing angry) Don't ask me to do that Padme. Make a motion in the Senate where that kind of a request belongs. I'm not your errand boy. I'm not anyone's errand boy!NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Don't ask me to do that Padme. Make a motion in the Senate where that kind of a request belongs. I'm not your errand boy. I'm not anyone's errand boy!

column3: PADME: What is it?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: What is it?

column3: ANAKIN: Nothing.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Nothing.

column3: PADME: Don't do this . . . don't shut me out. Let me help you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Don't do this . . . don't shut me out. Let me help you.

column3: ANAKIN: You can't help me . . . I'm trying to help you.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You can't help me . . . I'm trying to help you.

column3: ANAKIN: (continuing) I sense . . . there are things you are not telling me.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I sense . . . there are things you are not telling me.

column3: PADME: I sense there are things you are not telling me.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I sense there are things you are not telling me.

column3: PADME: (continuing) Hold me . . . like you did by the lake on Naboo so long ago . . . when there was nothing but our love ... No politics no plotting ... no war.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Hold me . . . like you did by the lake on Naboo so long ago . . . when there was nothing but our love ... No politics no plotting ... no war.

column3: ANAKIN: You wanted to see me Chancellor.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You wanted to see me Chancellor.

column3: PALPATINE: Yes Anakin! Come closer. I have good news. Our Clone Intelligence Units have discovered the location of General Grievous. He is hiding in the Utapau system.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Yes Anakin! Come closer. I have good news. Our Clone Intelligence Units have discovered the location of General Grievous. He is hiding in the Utapau system.

column3: ANAKIN: At last we'll be able to capture that monster and end this war.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: At last we'll be able to capture that monster and end this war.

column3: PALPATINE: I would worry about the collective wisdom of the Council if they didn't select you for this assignment. You are the best choice by far  but they can't always be trusted to do the right thing.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I would worry about the collective wisdom of the Council if they didn't select you for this assignment. You are the best choice by far  but they can't always be trusted to do the right thing.

column3: ANAKIN: They try.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They try.

column3: PALPATINE: Sit down (to his aides) Leave us.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Sit down  Leave us.

column3: PALPATINE: (continuing) Anakin you know I'm not able to rely on the Jedi Council. If they haven't included you in their plot they soon will.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin you know I'm not able to rely on the Jedi Council. If they haven't included you in their plot they soon will.

column3: ANAKIN: I'm not sure I understand.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I'm not sure I understand.

column3: PALPATINE: You must sense what I have come to suspect . . . the Jedi Council want control of the Republic . . . they're planning to betray me.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: You must sense what I have come to suspect . . . the Jedi Council want control of the Republic . . . they're planning to betray me.

column3: ANAKIN: I don't think . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I don't think . . .

column3: PALPATINE: Anakin search your feelings. You know don't you?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Anakin search your feelings. You know don't you?

column3: ANAKIN: I know they don't trust you . . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I know they don't trust you . . .

column3: PALPATINE: Or the Senate . . . or the Republic . . . or democracy for that matter.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Or the Senate . . . or the Republic . . . or democracy for that matter.

column3: ANAKIN: I have to admit my trust in them has been shaken.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I have to admit my trust in them has been shaken.

column3: PALPATINE: Why? They asked you to do something that made you feel dishonest didn't they?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Why? They asked you to do something that made you feel dishonest didn't they?

column3: PALPATINE: (continuing) They asked you to spy on me didn't they?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: They asked you to spy on me didn't they?

column3: ANAKIN: I don't know ... I don't know what to say.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: I don't know ... I don't know what to say.

column3: PALPATINE: Remember back to your early teachings. Anakin. "All those who gain power are afraid to lose it." Even the Jedi.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Remember back to your early teachings. Anakin. "All those who gain power are afraid to lose it." Even the Jedi.

column3: ANAKIN: The Jedi use their power for good.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Jedi use their power for good.

column3: PALPATINE: Good is a point of view Anakin. And the Jedi point of view is not the only valid one. The Dark Lords of the Sith believe in security and justice also yet they are considered by the Jedi to be. . .NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Good is a point of view Anakin. And the Jedi point of view is not the only valid one. The Dark Lords of the Sith believe in security and justice also yet they are considered by the Jedi to be. . .

column3: ANAKIN: . . . evil.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: . . . evil.

column3: PALPATINE: . . . from a Jedi's point of view. The Sith and the Jedi are similar in almost every way including their quest for greater power. The difference between the two is the Sith are not afraid of the dark side of the Force. That is why they are more powerful.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: . . . from a Jedi's point of view. The Sith and the Jedi are similar in almost every way including their quest for greater power. The difference between the two is the Sith are not afraid of the dark side of the Force. That is why they are more powerful.

column6: The Sith rely on their passion for their strength. They think inward only about themselves.

column3: PALPATINE: And the Jedi don't?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: And the Jedi don't?

column3: ANAKIN: The Jedi are selfless . . . they only care about others.NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: The Jedi are selfless . . . they only care about others.

column3: PALPATINE: Or so you've been trained to believe. Why is it then that they have asked you to do something you feel is wrong?NoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNoneNone
column6: Or so you've been trained to believe. Why is it then that they have asked you to do something you feel is wrong?
